### Bounce more

The change in scale is impressive, no doubt. However, we can build on the spring with another animation, and make a very receptive mascot in the process.

Always from the `svelte/motion` module import function `tweened`. From the `/easing` module, on the other hand, import a responsive timing function.

```svelte
<script>
	import { tweened, spring } from 'svelte/motion';
	import { elasticOut as easing } from 'svelte/easing';
</script>
```

Create an instance with an initial value of 1 and the chosen easing.

```js
const bounce = tweened(1, {
	duration: 1000,
	easing
});
```

Wrap the entire composition in a group element to scale everything from the center.

```svelte
<g transform="scale({$bounce})">
	<!-- mascot -->
</g>
```

Update the tween alongside the spring.

```js
const handleStart = () => {
	scale.set(1);
	bounce.set(1.1);
};

const handleEnd = () => {
	scale.set(0);
	bounce.set(1);
};
```

The effect is nice enough you might just consider additional group elements. Care to have the eyes pop?

```svelte
<!-- both circles -->
<g transform="scale({$bounce})">
	<circle r="2.5" />
</g>
```

### Touch events

This one is short and sweet. Consider two additional events: `touchstart` and `touchend`.

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
```svelte
<svg 
    on:touchstart={handleStart} 
    on:touchend={handleEnd}>
	<!--  -->
</svg>
```

The effect is not exactly the same, but at least you extend the interaction to support mobile devices. All that's needed is a tap. You decide how long to keep smiling.
